  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense under legislation in most countries. It involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Money laundering is typically prosecuted under criminal law and can result in significant legal penalties, including fines and imprisonment.\n\nIn many jurisdictions, money laundering is a serious crime covered by specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations. Financial institutions are required to implement measures to detect and prevent such activities.",
